Afghan Ariana Airlines to fly to Islamabad . Afghanistan ' s state - owned Ariana Airlines will open flights between the capital Kabul and the Pakistan capital of Islamabad , official Radio Afghanistan said on Tuesday . It said a protocol was signed on Monday between the Taleban - appointed deputy minister of civil aviation , whose name was not given , and representatives of the Pakistan government . It said the flights would start soon , but did not give further details . The Islamic Taleban movement took control of Kabul last month . Ariana , badly hit by the country ' s civil war , has maintained a sporadic domestic service and international flights to Delhi and Dubai . It evacuated two of its Boeing 727 airliners on Sunday after ousted government forces rocketed Kabul airport . 
